From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 01:00:00 +0200
Subject: PCI: qcom: enable SC8280XP QPS615 switch enumeration

Two changes bring up the QPS615 (TC9563) PCIe switch on pcie3a, both
matching the vendor SC8280XP tree.

Override the NO_SNOOP attribute on SC8280XP: the switch and the two
TC956x MACs behind it issue non-snooped TLPs the root complex cannot
handle coherently, which faults during enumeration.

Only recurse into PCI bridge nodes when collecting PERST#.
qcom_pcie_parse_perst() walked every child, including the TC956x endpoint
nodes whose PHY carries reset-gpios routed back through the host being
probed, so the PERST# request fails -EPROBE_DEFER and the port never
probes. Restrict the recursion to device_type = "pci" children, matching
qcom_pcie_parse_ports().

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
@@ -1503,6 +1503,7 @@ static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_2_9_0 = {
 static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_sc8280xp = {
 	.ops = &ops_1_21_0,
 	.no_l0s = true,
+	.override_no_snoop = true,
 };
 
 static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_fw_managed = {
@@ -1731,6 +1732,9 @@ static int qcom_pcie_parse_perst(struct qcom_pcie *pcie,
 
 parse_child_node:
 	for_each_available_child_of_node_scoped(np, child) {
+		if (!of_node_is_type(child, "pci"))
+			continue;
+
 		ret = qcom_pcie_parse_perst(pcie, port, child);
 		if (ret)
 			return ret;
